              "code": "```python\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\nclass LatencyVisualizer:\n    def __init__(self, data):\n        self.data = data\n\n    def plot_latency(self):\n        # Extract relevant data from the input data\n        latencies = [x['latency'] for x in self.data]\n        timestamps = [x['timestamp'] for x in self.data]\n\n        # Create a line plot of latency over time\n        plt.plot(timestamps, latencies)\n        plt.xlabel('Timestamp')\n        plt.ylabel('Latency (ms)')\n        plt.title('Latency Over Time')\n        plt.show()\n\n    def plot_latency_distribution(self):\n        # Extract relevant data from the input data\n        latencies = [x['latency'] for x in self.data]\n\n        # Create a histogram of latency values\n        plt.hist(latencies, bins=50)\n        plt.xlabel('Latency (ms)')\n        plt.ylabel('Frequency')\n        plt.title('Latency Distribution')\n        plt.show()\n\n# Example usage\ndata = [\n    {'latency': 10, 'timestamp': 1643723400},\n    {'latency': 20, 'timestamp': 1643723410},\n    {'latency': 15, 'timestamp': 1643723420},\n    # ...\n]\n\nvisualizer = LatencyVisualizer(data)\nvisualizer.plot_latency()\nvisualizer.plot_latency_distribution()\n```\n\n```",
